Class Closure

  • java.lang.Object
    • Closure

  • public class Closure
extends java.lang.Object
    Closure Conversion separate the function definition from the rest of the code. It: flatten the nest let rec; for each function, assign a label that will be used later on in the generated assembly; identify the parameters of the function; replace the call "f x1 ... xn" with a new instruction "apply_direct(l, (x1 ... xn))" where l is the label for f. After closure, the field closure_list contain all defined function in the program
